{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018L5tqxjjasB32i2EQmYvDy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive tapps-brain Composite Retrieval Scoring Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the tapps-brain codebase to understand how composite retrieval scoring works and where to add a `source_trust` signal. Here are all the key findings:\n\n---\n\n### 1. MemoryEntry Model Definition\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/models.py` (lines 82-232)\n\n**Key fields relevant to source tracking:**\n- **Line 34-40:** `MemorySource` enum with 4 values:\n  - `human` (0.95 confidence default)\n  - `agent` (0.6 confidence default)\n  - `inferred` (0.4 confidence default)\n  - `system` (0.9 confidence default)\n\n- **Line 94:** `source: MemorySource` field - stores the origin of the memory\n- **Line 95-97:** `source_agent: str` field - identifies which agent created it\n- **Line 88-93:** `confidence: float` field - explicit confidence (defaults derived from source via `_SOURCE_CONFIDENCE_DEFAULTS` at lines 56-61)\n\n**Current source-based defaults (lines 56-61):**\n```python\n_SOURCE_CONFIDENCE_DEFAULTS: dict[MemorySource, float] = {\n    MemorySource.human: 0.95,\n    MemorySource.agent: 0.6,\n    MemorySource.inferred: 0.4,\n    MemorySource.system: 0.9,\n}\n```\n\nThis is applied in the model validator at lines 188-195, which auto-fills confidence when explicitly set to -1.0.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Composite Retrieval Scoring System\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py` (lines 1-650)\n\n#### Scoring Weights (lines 56-67):\n```python\n_W_RELEVANCE = 0.40    # BM25 text relevance\n_W_CONFIDENCE = 0.30   # Time-decayed confidence\n_W_RECENCY = 0.15      # How recently updated\n_W_FREQUENCY = 0.15    # Access count (capped at 20)\n\n_BM25_NORM_K = 5.0     # Sigmoid normalization constant\n_FREQUENCY_CAP = 20.0  # Access count saturation\n```\n\n#### The Composite Score Calculation (lines 220-239):\n**Location:** `MemoryRetriever.search()` method around lines 220-230\n\n```python\n# Components computed separately:\nrelevance_norm = self._normalize_relevance(relevance_raw)  # 0-1 via sigmoid\nrecency = self._recency_score(entry, now)                 # 1/(1+days_since_update)\nfrequency = self._frequency_score(entry)                  # min(1.0, access_count/20)\neff_conf = calculate_decayed_confidence(entry, ...)       # Exponential decay by tier\n\n# COMPOSITE SCORE (line 225-230):\ncomposite = (\n    self._w_relevance * relevance_norm\n    + self._w_confidence * eff_conf\n    + self._w_recency * recency\n    + self._w_frequency * frequency\n)\n\n# PENALTY for superseded/temporal entries (line 233-234):\nif not temporally_valid:\n    composite *= 0.5\n\n# BONUS for exact key match (line 236-238):\nif entry.key == query.lower().replace(\" \", \"-\"):\n    composite += 0.1\n```\n\nThe final score is rounded to 4 decimals and stored in `ScoredMemory.score` (line 243).\n\n#### Configurable Weights (lines 121-136):\nThe `MemoryRetriever` constructor accepts a `scoring_config` object (from EPIC-010 profiles) that allows overriding all four weights via attributes: `relevance`, `confidence`, `recency`, `frequency`, `bm25_norm_k`, `frequency_cap`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. ScoredMemory Model\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py` (lines 44-52)\n\n```python\nclass ScoredMemory(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"A memory entry with retrieval scoring metadata.\"\"\"\n    \n    entry: MemoryEntry\n    score: float = Field(ge=0.0, description=\"Composite retrieval score.\")\n    effective_confidence: float = Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0, description=\"Time-decayed confidence.\")\n    bm25_relevance: float = Field(ge=0.0, description=\"Normalized text relevance.\")\n    stale: bool = Field(default=False, description=\"Whether the memory is stale.\")\n```\n\nThis is the return value from `search()` — each result includes the entry + 4 scoring components + stale flag.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Decay & Time-Decayed Confidence\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/decay.py` (lines 181-228)\n\n#### DecayConfig (lines 29-65):\nDefines tier-specific half-lives (architectural=180d, pattern=60d, procedural=30d, context=14d) and **source-based confidence ceilings** (not floors):\n\n```python\nclass DecayConfig(BaseModel):\n    # Hardcoded ceilings (lines 43-47):\n    human_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.95)\n    agent_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.85)\n    inferred_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.70)\n    system_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.95)\n    \n    # Profile-based overrides (EPIC-010):\n    profile_source_ceilings: dict[str, float] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    layer_confidence_floors: dict[str, float] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n```\n\n#### Decay Calculation (lines 181-228):\nThe `calculate_decayed_confidence()` function:\n1. Gets the source ceiling via `_get_ceiling(entry.source, config)` (lines 120-142)\n2. Gets the tier floor via `_get_confidence_floor(entry.tier, config)` (lines 145-154)\n3. Applies exponential or power-law decay based on days since update/reinforcement\n4. **Clamps result to [floor, ceiling]** — the ceiling is source-based!\n\n```python\ndecayed = entry.confidence * decay_factor\nreturn max(floor, min(ceiling, decayed))  # Line 228\n```\n\n**Key insight:** Source already influences decay bounds via ceilings, but there's **no explicit `source_trust` multiplier in the composite score itself**.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Configurable Scoring via Profiles\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/profile.py` (lines 48-72)\n\nThe `ScoringConfig` class defines the composite weight structure:\n\n```python\nclass ScoringConfig(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Composite scoring weight configuration.\"\"\"\n    \n    relevance: float = Field(default=0.40, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    confidence: float = Field(default=0.30, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    recency: float = Field(default=0.15, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    frequency: float = Field(default=0.15, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    bm25_norm_k: float = Field(default=5.0, ge=0.1)\n    frequency_cap: int = Field(default=20, ge=1)\n    \n    _WEIGHT_SUM_LO: float = 0.95\n    _WEIGHT_SUM_HI: float = 1.05\n    \n    @model_validator(mode=\"after\")\n    def _weights_sum_check(self) -> ScoringConfig:\n        # Validates sum is ~1.0 (lines 62-71)\n```\n\n**Note:** There is **no `source_trust` field** currently. The profile has `source_confidence` and `source_ceilings` dicts but these only affect decay, not composite scoring weights.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Memory Store Integration\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py`\n\n#### Search Method (lines 566-602):\n```python\ndef search(\n    self,\n    query: str,\n    tags: list[str] | None = None,\n    tier: str | None = None,\n    scope: str | None = None,\n    as_of: str | None = None,\n) -> list[MemoryEntry]:\n    \"\"\"FTS5-backed search with post-filters.\"\"\"\n    results = self._persistence.search(query)\n    # Apply tag, tier, scope, temporal filters\n    return results\n```\n\nThis does **FTS5 (Full-Text Search)** candidate retrieval only — the actual **ranked composite scoring happens in `MemoryRetriever.search()`**, not in the store.\n\n#### Save Method (lines 243-410):\nAccepts `source` and `source_agent` parameters (lines 248-249) and stores them on the entry. No scoring happens here — just persistence.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Retriever-Store Integration\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py`\n\nThe scoring flow (lines 138-263):\n\n1. **Input:** Query string + filters\n2. **Get candidates:** FTS5 via `store.search()` (lines 414-415) or full BM25 fallback (line 422)\n3. **Score each candidate:** For each entry:\n   - Calculate time-decayed confidence via `calculate_decayed_confidence()` (line 209)\n   - Compute BM25 relevance (line 221)\n   - Compute recency score (line 222)\n   - Compute frequency score (line 223)\n   - **Combine into composite** (lines 225-230)\n   - Apply penalties/bonuses (lines 232-238)\n4. **Filter:** Min confidence, temporal validity, tags\n5. **Sort:** By composite score descending (line 257)\n6. **Optionally rerank:** via `Reranker` if enabled (lines 260-261)\n7. **Return:** Top N `ScoredMemory` objects\n\n**Note:** The `entry.source` field is available at line 209 during scoring but is **NOT explicitly used** in the composite calculation (lines 225-230). Only the decayed confidence incorporates source info via ceilings.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Profile-Based Scoring Configuration in Store\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py` (lines 154-156)\n\nThe store resolves and holds the active profile:\n\n```python\nself._profile = self._resolve_profile(project_root, profile)\n```\n\nThis profile is accessible but **not passed to the MemoryRetriever** in the current code. The retriever gets `scoring_config` as a separate parameter (lines 99-128 in retrieval.py).\n\n---\n\n### 9. Decay Configuration from Profile\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py` (lines 226-237)\n\n```python\ndef _get_decay_config(self) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"Return DecayConfig derived from active profile.\"\"\"\n    if self._profile is not None:\n        try:\n            from tapps_brain.decay import decay_config_from_profile\n            return decay_config_from_profile(self._profile)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    from tapps_brain.decay import DecayConfig\n    return DecayConfig()\n```\n\nThis converts a profile to a `DecayConfig` instance but doesn't expose scoring weights.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Test Coverage for Scoring\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/unit/test_memory_retrieval.py` (lines 1-200+)\n\nTests cover:\n- Empty queries (line 97-101)\n- No matches (line 103-111)\n- Exact key match bonus (line 113-123)\n- High confidence ranks higher (line 125-145)\n- Recent memory ranks higher (line 147-167)\n- Contradicted entries filtered (line 169-190)\n- Result limits (line 192-198)\n\n**Note:** **No tests for source-based scoring** — the test helpers always use default sources or don't test source variations.\n\n---\n\n### 11. How to Add `source_trust` Signal\n\nBased on the architecture, here's where you'd add it:\n\n1. **ScoringConfig in profile.py** (lines 48-72):\n   - Add `source_trust: dict[str, float] = Field(default_factory=...)` to define per-source multipliers\n   - Or add a single `source_trust_factor: float = Field(default=0.0)` for a global source trust weight\n   - Update weight sum validation (line 62-71)\n\n2. **MemoryRetriever.__init__** (lines 95-136):\n   - Extract source trust config from `scoring_config` if present\n   - Store as instance variable `self._source_trust_multipliers` or similar\n\n3. **MemoryRetriever.search()** (lines 220-230):\n   - After computing composite score, apply source-based boost:\n     ```python\n     source_str = entry.source.value if isinstance(entry.source, MemorySource) else str(entry.source)\n     source_trust = self._source_trust_multipliers.get(source_str, 1.0)\n     composite *= source_trust\n     ```\n   - Or add source trust as a 5th weight component\n\n4. **DecayConfig/Profile** - Optional:\n   - Keep the existing `source_confidence_defaults` for initial confidence\n   - Add `source_trust_multipliers: dict[str, float]` for retrieval-time boosting\n   - Ensures separation of concerns: defaults vs. retrieval scoring\n\n---\n\n### 12. Summary of Key Files and Line Numbers\n\n| Purpose | File | Lines | Key Content |\n|---------|------|-------|------------|\n| Source enum & defaults | models.py | 34-61, 94-97 | `MemorySource`, `_SOURCE_CONFIDENCE_DEFAULTS`, `source` field |\n| Composite scoring | retrieval.py | 56-67, 220-230 | Weights, calculation formula |\n| ScoredMemory model | retrieval.py | 44-52 | Composite score structure |\n| Decay & ceilings | decay.py | 181-228, 120-142 | `calculate_decayed_confidence()`, source ceilings |\n| Scoring config model | profile.py | 48-72 | `ScoringConfig` (no source_trust yet) |\n| Store search integration | store.py | 566-602 | FTS5 retrieval (pre-scoring) |\n| Scorer instantiation | retrieval.py | 95-136 | Accepts `scoring_config` |\n\n---\n\nThis analysis provides everything needed to add a `source_trust` signal as a multiplier or weighted component in the composite retrieval score. The signal would apply after decay/confidence calculation and sit alongside the other four scoring dimensions (relevance, confidence, recency, frequency)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3c3ab9de44b46492 (use SendMessage with to: 'a3c3ab9de44b46492' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 80875\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 73849</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dfeb66a-ec06-46ac-b5f4-422c4dae48e2","uuid":"e684eb4e-79a6-4d1a-8ed6-4bc054faa072","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:44:50.833Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the tapps-brain codebase at C:\\cursor\\tapps-brain to understand how composite retrieval scoring works. I need to add a `source_trust` signal. \n\nLook for:\n1. The `_ranked_search()` method or similar ranked/composite scoring functions\n2. How `source` field is stored on memory entries (human, system, agent, inferred)\n3. The `MemoryEntry` model definition\n4. Any existing scoring/boosting logic (e.g., graph_boost, recency, access_count)\n5. The `search()` and `recall()` methods in the store\n6. Any config for scoring weights\n\nReport the exact file paths, line numbers, and relevant code snippets for all of these.","agentId":"a3c3ab9de44b46492","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive tapps-brain Composite Retrieval Scoring Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the tapps-brain codebase to understand how composite retrieval scoring works and where to add a `source_trust` signal. Here are all the key findings:\n\n---\n\n### 1. MemoryEntry Model Definition\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/models.py` (lines 82-232)\n\n**Key fields relevant to source tracking:**\n- **Line 34-40:** `MemorySource` enum with 4 values:\n  - `human` (0.95 confidence default)\n  - `agent` (0.6 confidence default)\n  - `inferred` (0.4 confidence default)\n  - `system` (0.9 confidence default)\n\n- **Line 94:** `source: MemorySource` field - stores the origin of the memory\n- **Line 95-97:** `source_agent: str` field - identifies which agent created it\n- **Line 88-93:** `confidence: float` field - explicit confidence (defaults derived from source via `_SOURCE_CONFIDENCE_DEFAULTS` at lines 56-61)\n\n**Current source-based defaults (lines 56-61):**\n```python\n_SOURCE_CONFIDENCE_DEFAULTS: dict[MemorySource, float] = {\n    MemorySource.human: 0.95,\n    MemorySource.agent: 0.6,\n    MemorySource.inferred: 0.4,\n    MemorySource.system: 0.9,\n}\n```\n\nThis is applied in the model validator at lines 188-195, which auto-fills confidence when explicitly set to -1.0.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Composite Retrieval Scoring System\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py` (lines 1-650)\n\n#### Scoring Weights (lines 56-67):\n```python\n_W_RELEVANCE = 0.40    # BM25 text relevance\n_W_CONFIDENCE = 0.30   # Time-decayed confidence\n_W_RECENCY = 0.15      # How recently updated\n_W_FREQUENCY = 0.15    # Access count (capped at 20)\n\n_BM25_NORM_K = 5.0     # Sigmoid normalization constant\n_FREQUENCY_CAP = 20.0  # Access count saturation\n```\n\n#### The Composite Score Calculation (lines 220-239):\n**Location:** `MemoryRetriever.search()` method around lines 220-230\n\n```python\n# Components computed separately:\nrelevance_norm = self._normalize_relevance(relevance_raw)  # 0-1 via sigmoid\nrecency = self._recency_score(entry, now)                 # 1/(1+days_since_update)\nfrequency = self._frequency_score(entry)                  # min(1.0, access_count/20)\neff_conf = calculate_decayed_confidence(entry, ...)       # Exponential decay by tier\n\n# COMPOSITE SCORE (line 225-230):\ncomposite = (\n    self._w_relevance * relevance_norm\n    + self._w_confidence * eff_conf\n    + self._w_recency * recency\n    + self._w_frequency * frequency\n)\n\n# PENALTY for superseded/temporal entries (line 233-234):\nif not temporally_valid:\n    composite *= 0.5\n\n# BONUS for exact key match (line 236-238):\nif entry.key == query.lower().replace(\" \", \"-\"):\n    composite += 0.1\n```\n\nThe final score is rounded to 4 decimals and stored in `ScoredMemory.score` (line 243).\n\n#### Configurable Weights (lines 121-136):\nThe `MemoryRetriever` constructor accepts a `scoring_config` object (from EPIC-010 profiles) that allows overriding all four weights via attributes: `relevance`, `confidence`, `recency`, `frequency`, `bm25_norm_k`, `frequency_cap`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. ScoredMemory Model\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py` (lines 44-52)\n\n```python\nclass ScoredMemory(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"A memory entry with retrieval scoring metadata.\"\"\"\n    \n    entry: MemoryEntry\n    score: float = Field(ge=0.0, description=\"Composite retrieval score.\")\n    effective_confidence: float = Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0, description=\"Time-decayed confidence.\")\n    bm25_relevance: float = Field(ge=0.0, description=\"Normalized text relevance.\")\n    stale: bool = Field(default=False, description=\"Whether the memory is stale.\")\n```\n\nThis is the return value from `search()` — each result includes the entry + 4 scoring components + stale flag.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Decay & Time-Decayed Confidence\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/decay.py` (lines 181-228)\n\n#### DecayConfig (lines 29-65):\nDefines tier-specific half-lives (architectural=180d, pattern=60d, procedural=30d, context=14d) and **source-based confidence ceilings** (not floors):\n\n```python\nclass DecayConfig(BaseModel):\n    # Hardcoded ceilings (lines 43-47):\n    human_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.95)\n    agent_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.85)\n    inferred_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.70)\n    system_confidence_ceiling: float = Field(default=0.95)\n    \n    # Profile-based overrides (EPIC-010):\n    profile_source_ceilings: dict[str, float] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    layer_confidence_floors: dict[str, float] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n```\n\n#### Decay Calculation (lines 181-228):\nThe `calculate_decayed_confidence()` function:\n1. Gets the source ceiling via `_get_ceiling(entry.source, config)` (lines 120-142)\n2. Gets the tier floor via `_get_confidence_floor(entry.tier, config)` (lines 145-154)\n3. Applies exponential or power-law decay based on days since update/reinforcement\n4. **Clamps result to [floor, ceiling]** — the ceiling is source-based!\n\n```python\ndecayed = entry.confidence * decay_factor\nreturn max(floor, min(ceiling, decayed))  # Line 228\n```\n\n**Key insight:** Source already influences decay bounds via ceilings, but there's **no explicit `source_trust` multiplier in the composite score itself**.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Configurable Scoring via Profiles\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/profile.py` (lines 48-72)\n\nThe `ScoringConfig` class defines the composite weight structure:\n\n```python\nclass ScoringConfig(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Composite scoring weight configuration.\"\"\"\n    \n    relevance: float = Field(default=0.40, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    confidence: float = Field(default=0.30, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    recency: float = Field(default=0.15, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    frequency: float = Field(default=0.15, ge=0.0, le=1.0)\n    bm25_norm_k: float = Field(default=5.0, ge=0.1)\n    frequency_cap: int = Field(default=20, ge=1)\n    \n    _WEIGHT_SUM_LO: float = 0.95\n    _WEIGHT_SUM_HI: float = 1.05\n    \n    @model_validator(mode=\"after\")\n    def _weights_sum_check(self) -> ScoringConfig:\n        # Validates sum is ~1.0 (lines 62-71)\n```\n\n**Note:** There is **no `source_trust` field** currently. The profile has `source_confidence` and `source_ceilings` dicts but these only affect decay, not composite scoring weights.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Memory Store Integration\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py`\n\n#### Search Method (lines 566-602):\n```python\ndef search(\n    self,\n    query: str,\n    tags: list[str] | None = None,\n    tier: str | None = None,\n    scope: str | None = None,\n    as_of: str | None = None,\n) -> list[MemoryEntry]:\n    \"\"\"FTS5-backed search with post-filters.\"\"\"\n    results = self._persistence.search(query)\n    # Apply tag, tier, scope, temporal filters\n    return results\n```\n\nThis does **FTS5 (Full-Text Search)** candidate retrieval only — the actual **ranked composite scoring happens in `MemoryRetriever.search()`**, not in the store.\n\n#### Save Method (lines 243-410):\nAccepts `source` and `source_agent` parameters (lines 248-249) and stores them on the entry. No scoring happens here — just persistence.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Retriever-Store Integration\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py`\n\nThe scoring flow (lines 138-263):\n\n1. **Input:** Query string + filters\n2. **Get candidates:** FTS5 via `store.search()` (lines 414-415) or full BM25 fallback (line 422)\n3. **Score each candidate:** For each entry:\n   - Calculate time-decayed confidence via `calculate_decayed_confidence()` (line 209)\n   - Compute BM25 relevance (line 221)\n   - Compute recency score (line 222)\n   - Compute frequency score (line 223)\n   - **Combine into composite** (lines 225-230)\n   - Apply penalties/bonuses (lines 232-238)\n4. **Filter:** Min confidence, temporal validity, tags\n5. **Sort:** By composite score descending (line 257)\n6. **Optionally rerank:** via `Reranker` if enabled (lines 260-261)\n7. **Return:** Top N `ScoredMemory` objects\n\n**Note:** The `entry.source` field is available at line 209 during scoring but is **NOT explicitly used** in the composite calculation (lines 225-230). Only the decayed confidence incorporates source info via ceilings.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Profile-Based Scoring Configuration in Store\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py` (lines 154-156)\n\nThe store resolves and holds the active profile:\n\n```python\nself._profile = self._resolve_profile(project_root, profile)\n```\n\nThis profile is accessible but **not passed to the MemoryRetriever** in the current code. The retriever gets `scoring_config` as a separate parameter (lines 99-128 in retrieval.py).\n\n---\n\n### 9. Decay Configuration from Profile\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py` (lines 226-237)\n\n```python\ndef _get_decay_config(self) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"Return DecayConfig derived from active profile.\"\"\"\n    if self._profile is not None:\n        try:\n            from tapps_brain.decay import decay_config_from_profile\n            return decay_config_from_profile(self._profile)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    from tapps_brain.decay import DecayConfig\n    return DecayConfig()\n```\n\nThis converts a profile to a `DecayConfig` instance but doesn't expose scoring weights.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Test Coverage for Scoring\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/unit/test_memory_retrieval.py` (lines 1-200+)\n\nTests cover:\n- Empty queries (line 97-101)\n- No matches (line 103-111)\n- Exact key match bonus (line 113-123)\n- High confidence ranks higher (line 125-145)\n- Recent memory ranks higher (line 147-167)\n- Contradicted entries filtered (line 169-190)\n- Result limits (line 192-198)\n\n**Note:** **No tests for source-based scoring** — the test helpers always use default sources or don't test source variations.\n\n---\n\n### 11. How to Add `source_trust` Signal\n\nBased on the architecture, here's where you'd add it:\n\n1. **ScoringConfig in profile.py** (lines 48-72):\n   - Add `source_trust: dict[str, float] = Field(default_factory=...)` to define per-source multipliers\n   - Or add a single `source_trust_factor: float = Field(default=0.0)` for a global source trust weight\n   - Update weight sum validation (line 62-71)\n\n2. **MemoryRetriever.__init__** (lines 95-136):\n   - Extract source trust config from `scoring_config` if present\n   - Store as instance variable `self._source_trust_multipliers` or similar\n\n3. **MemoryRetriever.search()** (lines 220-230):\n   - After computing composite score, apply source-based boost:\n     ```python\n     source_str = entry.source.value if isinstance(entry.source, MemorySource) else str(entry.source)\n     source_trust = self._source_trust_multipliers.get(source_str, 1.0)\n     composite *= source_trust\n     ```\n   - Or add source trust as a 5th weight component\n\n4. **DecayConfig/Profile** - Optional:\n   - Keep the existing `source_confidence_defaults` for initial confidence\n   - Add `source_trust_multipliers: dict[str, float]` for retrieval-time boosting\n   - Ensures separation of concerns: defaults vs. retrieval scoring\n\n---\n\n### 12. Summary of Key Files and Line Numbers\n\n| Purpose | File | Lines | Key Content |\n|---------|------|-------|------------|\n| Source enum & defaults | models.py | 34-61, 94-97 | `MemorySource`, `_SOURCE_CONFIDENCE_DEFAULTS`, `source` field |\n| Composite scoring | retrieval.py | 56-67, 220-230 | Weights, calculation formula |\n| ScoredMemory model | retrieval.py | 44-52 | Composite score structure |\n| Decay & ceilings | decay.py | 181-228, 120-142 | `calculate_decayed_confidence()`, source ceilings |\n| Scoring config model | profile.py | 48-72 | `ScoringConfig` (no source_trust yet) |\n| Store search integration | store.py | 566-602 | FTS5 retrieval (pre-scoring) |\n| Scorer instantiation | retrieval.py | 95-136 | Accepts `scoring_config` |\n\n---\n\nThis analysis provides everything needed to add a `source_trust` signal as a multiplier or weighted component in the composite retrieval score. The signal would apply after decay/confidence calculation and sit alongside the other four scoring dimensions (relevance, confidence, recency, frequency)."}],"totalDurationMs":73849,"totalTokens":80875,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2082,"cache_read_input_tokens":74997,"output_tokens":3796,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2082},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
